-- National City posts 4th-quarter loss
-- 
-- Tue Jan 22, 2008 7:19am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/22/us-nationalcity-results-idUSWNAS703520080122

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - National City Corp NCC.N, a large U.S. Midwest regional bank battered by the housing downturn, on Tuesday posted a $333 million fourth-quarter loss, hurt by mounting credit losses and write-downs. 

 The loss for Cleveland-based bank was 53 cents per share, and compared with a profit of $842 million, or $1.36 per share, a year earlier. (Reporting by Jonathan Stempel; Editing by  Derek Caney )